    "gallery_text": "L\u00e9onard Chailleau was a French sculptor active in central Italy, where he was known as Leonardo Scaglia, or simply il Francese (\u201cthe French\u201d). Known as a skilled woodcarver, he produced work for numerous church interiors in the Marche and Umbria regions. This fluid sketch of an angel blowing into a serpentine horn was likely a preliminary design for a sculpture as part of an ecclesiastic commission. Angels and putti feature prominently in Chailleau\u2019s extant work.",
